-----CREATING A TABLE-----

- CREATE TABLE
    - used to create a table
        - ex: CREATE TABLE table_name (
              column1 datatype,
              column2 datatype,
              column3 datatype,
              ....
              );

    - You can mark a field as a primary key using PRIMARY_KEY
    - You can mark fields as not being nullable
    - You can also mark fields as being an auto-incremented field (this must be an integer data type)
        - ex: CREATE TABLE table_name (
            column1 INT NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
            column2 datatype,
            column3 datatype NOT NULL,
            ....
            PRIMARY KEY (column1)
            );

        - ex: CREATE TABLE advertisements (
              AdId int NOT NULL AUTO_INCREMENT,
              Title varchar(50) NOT NULL,
              MagicCode varchar(9),
              PercentOff float NOT NULL,
              PRIMARY KEY(AdId)
              );
